Source Content 
https://www.atlassian.com/git/tutorials/learn-git-with-bitbucket-cloud

git config - this user sets the auther name and email id to be used with commits
git config --global user.name "somnath"
git config --global user.email "somnath.jagadale@gmail.com"


git init - it used to start the new repository 
git init /home4/somanath/NTRSource


git clone - it obtain the repository from the existing clone 
git clone https://github.com/opt/Roamware/NTR.git


git commit - this commands record or snapshot the file permanently in the version history
git commit -m "BRG and ABS changes" 

git commit -a this commands record or snapshot the file permanently in the version history, also adds the file in stagging area


git diff - this commands shows the file difference which are not yet changed
git diff -stagged - this command shows the file difference between the files in the stagging area and the latest version present.
